---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout title="Scrabble Words Ending in QI — The Rarest Ending" description="Explore words ending in QI in Scrabble. QI itself is the key word — learn how to play it effectively for maximum points on premium squares." keywords="words ending in qi, qi scrabble word, scrabble qi, qi without u, q words scrabble, qi ending words">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Scrabble Words Ending in QI — The Rarest Ending",
    "description": "Explore words ending in QI and master the most valuable 2-letter word in Scrabble.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-22",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" }
  })}></script>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What words end in QI in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "QI (11pts) is essentially the only standard word ending in QI. In SOWPODS, WAQF-derived forms and QI itself are valid. It remains the rarest word ending in competitive Scrabble." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is QI the only word ending in QI?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "In the TWL dictionary used in North American tournaments, QI is the only word with this ending. SOWPODS includes a few additional entries, but QI is by far the most commonly played." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "How do you play QI effectively in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Play QI on a Double or Triple Letter Score under the Q for 20-31 points. It pairs well as a parallel play forming two 2-letter words simultaneously. Also use it to hook onto existing I words." }}
    ]
  })}></script>

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-white">← Blog</a> <span class="mx-2">›</span> <span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words Ending in QI</h1>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-8">Updated June 22, 2026 · 3 min read</p>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-8">QI is a game-changer. This tiny 2-letter word — meaning "life force" in Chinese philosophy — is worth 11 points base and is one of the most played words in competitive Scrabble. Let's look at how to maximize its value.</p>

      <div class="border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10 rounded-xl p-6 mb-10 grid grid-cols-3 gap-4 text-center">
        <div><span class="text-amber-400 text-2xl font-bold">11pts</span><br><span class="text-gray-400 text-sm">QI base score</span></div>
        <div><span class="text-amber-400 text-2xl font-bold">10pts</span><br><span class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Q tile value</span></div>
        <div><span class="text-amber-400 text-2xl font-bold">31pts</span><br><span class="text-gray-400 text-sm">QI on TLS (Q)</span></div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">The QI Word Entry</h2>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-8">
        <table class="w-full border border-gray-700 rounded-lg text-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-800"><tr><th class="p-3 text-left text-gray-300">Word</th><th class="p-3 text-left text-gray-300">Points</th><th class="p-3 text-left text-gray-300">Dictionary</th><th class="p-3 text-left text-gray-300">Definition</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="p-3 text-white font-bold">QI</td><td class="p-3 text-blue-400">11</td><td class="p-3 text-gray-300">TWL + SOWPODS</td><td class="p-3 text-gray-400">The vital force in Chinese philosophy</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
        <p class="text-blue-400 font-semibold mb-2">Quick Insight</p>
        <p class="text-gray-300">QI was added to the Official Scrabble Players Dictionary in 2006. Before that, players with Q and no U were nearly stuck. Today, QI is among the most commonly played words in tournament games, appearing in roughly 1 in 3 competitive matches.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Premium Square Scoring</h2>

      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">QI's power comes from placement. Here's what it scores on different premium squares:</p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-8">
        <table class="w-full border border-gray-700 rounded-lg text-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-800"><tr><th class="p-3 text-left text-gray-300">Placement</th><th class="p-3 text-left text-gray-300">Score</th><th class="p-3 text-left text-gray-300">Calculation</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="p-3 text-gray-300">No premium</td><td class="p-3 text-blue-400">11</td><td class="p-3 text-gray-400">Q(10) + I(1) = 11</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="p-3 text-gray-300">DLS on Q</td><td class="p-3 text-blue-400">21</td><td class="p-3 text-gray-400">Q(20) + I(1) = 21</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="p-3 text-gray-300">TLS on Q</td><td class="p-3 text-blue-400">31</td><td class="p-3 text-gray-400">Q(30) + I(1) = 31</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="p-3 text-gray-300">DWS</td><td class="p-3 text-blue-400">22</td><td class="p-3 text-gray-400">(10+1) × 2 = 22</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="p-3 text-gray-300">TWS</td><td class="p-3 text-blue-400">33</td><td class="p-3 text-gray-400">(10+1) × 3 = 33</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Playing QI</h2>

      <div class="border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
        <p class="text-purple-400 font-semibold mb-2">Strategy Tips</p>
        <ul class="text-gray-300 space-y-2 list-disc pl-5">
          <li><span class="text-purple-400 font-bold">Parallel plays:</span> Place QI next to an existing word so both the Q and I form valid 2-letter crosswords. This can double your score.</li>
          <li><span class="text-purple-400 font-bold">Hook onto I:</span> If the board has a word ending in I, drop Q in front for an instant 11+ points.</li>
          <li><span class="text-purple-400 font-bold">Don't hold Q too long:</span> Play QI early if no U appears. A stuck Q at game-end costs you 10 points.</li>
          <li><span class="text-purple-400 font-bold">QI + another word:</span> The best QI plays also form a second word simultaneously, like QI/IS or QI/IT.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Other Q-Without-U Words</h2>

      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">If you have Q without U, these words also save you:</p>

      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 mb-10">
        <span class="bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 rounded-lg px-3 py-2"><span class="text-white font-bold">QI</span> <span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 rounded-lg px-3 py-2"><span class="text-white font-bold">QOPH</span> <span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">18pts</span></span>
        <span class="bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 rounded-lg px-3 py-2"><span class="text-white font-bold">QADI</span> <span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">14pts</span></span>
        <span class="bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 rounded-lg px-3 py-2"><span class="text-white font-bold">QAID</span> <span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">14pts</span></span>
        <span class="bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 rounded-lg px-3 py-2"><span class="text-white font-bold">QANAT</span> <span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">14pts</span></span>
        <span class="bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 rounded-lg px-3 py-2"><span class="text-white font-bold">QINTAR</span> <span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">15pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-950/10 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
        <p class="text-indigo-400 font-semibold mb-2">Related Reads</p>
        <ul class="text-gray-300 space-y-1">
          <li><a href="/blog/words-containing-q" class="text-indigo-400 hover:underline">Words Containing Q</a></li>
          <li><a href="/blog/common-foreign-origin-scrabble-words" class="text-indigo-400 hover:underline">Common Foreign-Origin Scrabble Words</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-blue-800/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl p-6 text-center mb-10">
        <p class="text-white font-semibold mb-2">Got Q Without U?</p>
        <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">Our solver finds every Q-without-U play on your rack — including parallel QI placements.</p>
        <a href="/" class="inline-block bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-500 text-white font-semibold px-6 py-3 rounded-lg transition">Try the Word Finder →</a>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 pt-8 mt-12">
        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-4">Related Articles</p>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/words-containing-q" class="block border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 rounded-lg p-4 transition"><span class="text-white">Words Containing Q</span><br><span class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Complete Q word guide including Q-without-U</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/words-ending-in-xi" class="block border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 rounded-lg p-4 transition"><span class="text-white">Words Ending in XI</span><br><span class="text-gray-400 text-sm">TAXI, MAXI and other XI-endings</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="mt-8"><a href="/blog" class="text-gray-400 hover:text-white text-sm">← Back to Blog</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
